    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='Based on the provided financial and operational disclosures, here are the segment descriptions, revenue drivers, and key performance indicators (KPIs) for the Space, Connectivity, and AI segments:\n\n### 1. Space Segment\n*   **Segment Description:** Designs, manufactures, and launches reusable rockets (including Falcon 9, Falcon Heavy, and the next-generation Starship) to provide high-cadence, reliable, and affordable access to space at an unprecedented scale. It serves as a foundational strategic enabler for the company\'s long-term growth by allocating significant internal launch capacity to the Connectivity and AI segments.\n*   **Revenue Drivers:** \n    *   **Launch Services:** Revenue from customer launches, recognized at a point in time.\n    *   **Launch & Development:** Revenue from long-term contracts (primarily for government customers), recognized over time or on a percentage-of-completion basis.\n    *   *Note:* The segment\'s revenue **only** reflects external customer launches. Internal launches dedicated to deploying Starlink or AI satellites are capitalized within their respective segments and do not generate Space segment revenue.\n*   **Key Performance Indicators (KPIs):**\n    *   **Financial Metrics:** Revenue, Loss from operations, Segment Adjusted EBITDA, and Capital Expenditures.\n    *   **Operational/Strategic Metrics:** Launch cadence, payload capacity, reusability rates, and R&D funding specifically allocated to the Starship launch vehicle program. Revenue mix between Launch Services and Launch & Development.\n\n### 2. Connectivity Segment\n*   **Segment Description:** Operates a worldwide high-speed, low-latency broadband data and communications network powered by over 9,600 Starlink broadband and mobile satellites in Low-Earth Orbit (LEO). It delivers internet and communications services to consumer, enterprise, and government customers across 164 countries, territories, and markets.\n*   **Revenue Drivers:**\n    *   **Consumer Broadband:** Residential subscriptions (represented over 60% of segment revenue in 2025).\n    *   **Enterprise & Government:** Long-term contracts for enterprise clients and "Starshield" (a secure satellite network for national security/government applications).\n    *   **Starlink Mobile:** Revenue-sharing arrangements with Mobile Network Operator (MNO) partners for satellite-to-mobile texting and over-the-top voice services.\n    *   **Products:** Hardware/terminal sales (all company "Products" revenue is attributable to this segment).\n    *   *Growth Catalysts:* Subscriber acquisition, increasing enterprise adoption, and continuous improvements in network efficiency.\n*   **Key Performance Indicators (KPIs):**\n    *   **Financial Metrics:** Revenue, Income from operations, Segment Adjusted EBITDA, Capital Expenditures, and Depreciation (tied to the number of satellites placed in orbit).\n    *   **Operational Metrics:** \n        *   Total Starlink Subscribers (approx. 10.3 million).\n        *   Monthly unique mobile devices connected (approx. 7.4 million).\n        *   Network performance: Median latency (approx. 25 milliseconds) and median peak-hour download speeds (225 Mbps for residential users).\n        *   Satellite constellation size (approx. 9,600 LEO satellites).\n\n### 3. AI Segment\n*   **Segment Description:** Operates a highly vertically integrated AI platform spanning gigawatt-scale AI compute infrastructure (e.g., the COLOSSUS II facility), the truth-seeking frontier AI model "Grok," AI solutions for consumer and enterprise customers, and "X" (a real-time information, entertainment, and free speech platform). The segment also includes future strategies for orbital AI compute satellites to handle energy-intensive inference workloads.\n*   **Revenue Drivers:**\n    *   **Advertising:** Revenue generated via the X platform.\n    *   **AI Solutions & Infrastructure:** Compute infrastructure hosting and AI applications.\n    *   **Subscriptions:** Consumer and enterprise subscriptions for X and Grok.\n    *   *Growth Catalysts:* Capturing the $26.5 trillion potential market opportunity for AI, scaling power-efficient compute infrastructure to support the convergence toward Artificial General Intelligence (AGI), and prioritizing aggressive investment over short-term profitability.\n*   **Key Performance Indicators (KPIs):**\n    *   **Financial Metrics:** Revenue, Loss from operations, Segment Adjusted EBITDA, and Capital Expenditures (which are massive and scaling as quickly as power and compute can be deployed).\n    *   **Cost & Investment Metrics:** R&D expenses (heavily driven by GPU hardware depreciation, cloud computing, and data center infrastructure expansion costs).\n    *   **Strategic Metrics:** Compute infrastructure deployment scale, power efficiency, and the timeline to translate multi-year CapEx deployments into sustained positive Segment Adjusted EBITDA.',
