d of the subscription term (which typically ranges from month-to-month to one year).\n*   **Data Licensing:** Arrangements granting access to historical and real-time IP on the X platform are recognized based on the nature of the performance obligation:\n    *   *Historical IP:* Recognized at a **point in time**.\n    *   *Future IP:* Recognized **over time** on a straight-line basis over the period the data is provided (ranging from month-to-month to two years).\n    *   *Multiple Obligations:* If a contract contains multiple performance obligations, revenue is allocated on a relative basis using standalone selling prices and recognized as each specific obligation is satisfied. \n*(Note: While API access to Grok models is listed as a revenue source for AI solutions, the specific recognition mechanics for the API were cut off in the provided text).*',
