ncome, $16 in upper-middle, $9 in lower-middle/low-income markets).\n    *   *Mobile:* Global weighted average of **$8/month** ($18 in high-income, $5 in upper-middle, $2 in lower-middle/low-income markets).\n\n### 4. Growth Rates\n*   **Subscriber Growth (Year-over-Year):**\n    *   **Q1 2026 vs. Q1 2025:** Up **105%** (also cited as **104.7%** in the MD&A narrative).\n    *   **Q1 2025 vs. Q1 2024:** Up **91%**.\n    *   **FY 2025 vs. FY 2024:** Up **99.9%**.\n    *   **FY 2024 vs. FY 2023:** Up **96.5%**.\n*   **ARPU Decline (Year-over-Year):**\n    *   **Q1 2026 vs. Q1 2025:** Declined by **22.9%**.\n    *   **FY 2025 vs. FY 2024:** Declined by **11.2%**.\n    *   **FY 2024 vs. FY 2023:** Declined by **8.1%**.\n*   **Connectivity Segment Financial Growth:**\n    *   **Revenue:** Grew **31.6%** in Q1 2026 (to $3,257M); grew **49.8%** in FY 2025 (to $11,387M); grew **96.4%** in FY 2024.\n    *   **Income from Operations:** Grew **120.4%** in FY 2025 (to $4,423M). In Q1 2026, it increased by $155M to $1,188M.\n    *   **Adjusted EBITDA:** Grew **86.2%** in FY 2025 (to $7,168M). In Q1 2026, it increased by $469M to $2,087M.\n\n### 5. Forward-Looking Guidance\n*   **ARPU Trajectory:** Management explicitly expects Starlink Subscriber ARPU to **continue to decline over the next few years**. This is driven by:\n    1.  The portion of the subscriber base outside North America continuing to grow.\n    2.  The addition of lower-priced service plans.\n    3.  Adjustments to monthly service plan fees for broadband offerings to make the service affordable/accessible globally.\n*   **Offsetting ARPU Declines:** The company expects the negative impact of declining ARPU to be offset by increased scale and technological advancements in launch, satellite, and user terminal operations, which will support overall revenue growth and cost reduction.\n*   **Subscriber Acquisition Strategy:** Growth will be driven by expanding the consumer distribution network across thousands of authorized global retail stores and executing region-specific marketing campaigns to increase brand awareness.\n*   **Enterprise & Mobility Expansion:** The company sees a "large opportunity" to grow the enterprise connectivity market (aviation, maritime, land mobility) and believes it has a "differentiated right to win" in-motion environments where legacy solutions suffer from outages and coverage gaps.\n*   **Launch Capacity Allocation:** The Space segment will continue to allocate a "significant amount" of launch capacity to the Connectivity segment to support constellation deployment.',
