        output='Based on the provided prospectus and S-1 excerpts, here are the disclosed metrics and statistics categorized by your requested areas:\n\n### 1. AI Segment User Metrics & Combined MAU Methodology\n*   **Total Active Accounts:** Over **1.3 billion** supported accounts were active in the last twelve months ended March 31, 2026 (up from over 1.1 billion as of December 31, 2025).\n*   **Combined MAUs:** Approximately **550 million** Monthly Active Users (MAUs) across Grok and X as of March 31, 2026 (up from ~520 million as of December 31, 2025).\n*   **Calculation Methodology:** MAU counts unique, registered users who interact with Grok or X via web or mobile at least once in a 30-day period. The company uses sign-in traffic to deduplicate users who access *both* platforms so they are not double-counted. The company tracks Grok AI feature usage versus non-usage based on server request sources. Management notes this is an "estimate" as it may not capture all instances of duplication.\n*   **Strategic Focus:** Management explicitly states they prioritize revenue and operating margin over the primary objective of simply growing or maintaining MAU levels.\n\n### 2. X Platform Monthly Active Users & Activity\n*   **X-Specific MAUs:** While the 550 million figure represents the *combined* deduplicated MAUs of X and Grok, X\'s standalone user base is referred to in the Business section as having **"hundreds of millions of MAUs."**\n*   **Daily Content Generation:** The platforms generate approximately **350 million daily posts**.\n*   **Platform Evolution:** Engagement is being driven by X\'s evolution into an "Everything App," integrating real-time information, media, long-form video, X Chat (end-to-end encrypted), and the X Money product (launched in beta in November 2025) to increase utility and monetization potential.\n\n### 3. Grok Usage Metrics\n*   **Grok AI Feature MAUs:** Approximately **117 million** MAUs used Grok’s AI features as of March 31, 2026.\n*   **Image & Video Generation:** Grok\'s "Imagine" system produced an average of **10 billion images** and over **2 billion videos** per month for the quarter ending March 31, 2026.\n*   **Grok Paid Subscribers:** Approximately **1.9 million** active paid subscribers for SuperGrok, SuperGrok Heavy, and SuperGrok Lite (as of March 31, 2026).\n*   **Usage Fluctuations (Risk Factor):** The company discloses that download and usage metrics for Grok can "fluctuate significantly" (including periods of decreased downloads/activity) in response to competitor model releases and product update cycles.\n\n### 4. Advertising Metrics\n*   **Revenue Growth:** Advertising revenue increased by **$116 million** for the year ended December 31, 2025, compared to the prior year, driven by increased spend from partners on X.\n*   **Advertiser Engagement Metrics:** The company provides advertisers with specific performance metrics, including: **impressions, price per ad, clicks, and conversions.**\n*   **Pricing & Formats:** Ads are sold via an auction process (with some fixed-price reserved inventory) and performance-based pricing (paying only for actions like clicks/engagements). Formats include Promoted Ads, Vertical Video Ads, Collection Ads, X Amplify, and Takeovers.\n*   **Seasonality:** Ad spend is typically highest in Q4 (end-of-year spending) and lowest in Q1.\n*   **Market Opportunity:** Global digital advertising spending totaled **$600 billion** in 2025 (per S&P Global Market Intelligence).\n*   **Platform Upgrades:** A rebuilt, AI-powered advertising platform (X Ads Manager) began a phased roll-out in April 2026 to improve targeting, campaign creation, and real-time monitoring.\n\n### 5. Engagement Statistics & Monetization\n*   **Total Paid Subscribers:** Reached approximately **6.3 million** active paid subscribers as of March 31, 2026. This comprises **4.4 million** X Premium/Premium+ subscribers and **1.9 million** Grok subscribers.\n*   **Consumer AI Subscription TAM:*